body:
Killing Eve S2 premiere

So I was looking through Killing Eve’s IMDb page and noticed that S2 episodes were already listed, although untitled. I found out that:

• there will also be 8 episodes

• both sandra and jodie will appear in 7 of them

• they both won’t appear on episode 1

• the cast listed in s2e1 are all new faces

• some characters listed are: Teacher, Supermarket Husband, M15 Colleague, Hugo, etc.

• some of the new characters will be played by the new cast members announced earlier on

• so… are we going to get a flashback episode for the s2 premiere?

body:
My Top 10 female characters:

Just because there are so many fascinating characters out there!

1. Villanelle <3 <3 <3

2. Lexa of course!

3. Maeve Millay with probably the best gif ever

4. Veronica Mars, first show I got into!

5. Bea Smith you’re still missed!

6. Julia Wicker + Marina Andrieski : an amazing duo!

7. Lenny Busker, such a fascinating villain 

8. Cersei Lannister played by a brilliant actress

9. Nell Crain, because the Bent Neck Lady episode broke me

10. All the clones !!!! 

If anyone feel like doing a list of their own and making us discover great characters and shows, please do!

body:
Villanelle as on the Spectrum

I present to you, my latest KE headcanon - High Functioning Autistic Villanelle. I very recently came to the conclusion that I myself am almost definitively on the spectrum, and in the process of exploring that I’ve been drawing a lot of parallels between my own experiences and the way Villanelle moves through the world. Some specifics -

No thought filter/tendency to overshare

- “I mean I masturbate about you a lot”

Feelings of extreme isolation

- Always begging Constantine to hang out or inviting herself over to Eve’s for dinner

Obsessive special interests

- Eve, fashion, the very special care she takes in performing her job functions

Befriends people who are older or younger than her most frequently

- Constantine, Eve, Irina

Treats friends as pawns

- Irina, Nadia, and her compulsively violent prison friend whose name escapes me at the moment

Excellent at social camouflage

- this is what makes her so good at her job, in my option

Relationship based fixations and escapism

- Eve, Anna

Lack of impulse control

- Um…everything?? Villanelle is always in primal mode

Rejection of social norms

- the fact she’s chill with killing people for a living

Very frank and literal

- Her responses every time someone asks her if she’s going to kill them, hahaha.

Difficulty processing emotions

- This is one that I think is going to come into play a bunch in S2 while we deal with the aftermath of Eve stabbing her

Anyway, I’m sure not everyone will agree but I personally think a lot of this is very in character behavior for Villanelle and could easily be canonized should the writers ever decide to explore it.
